					<p class='chart__copy'>Binge and heavy drinking in the United States climbed <mark class='mark--binge'>8.9 percent</mark> and <mark class='mark--heavy'>17.2 percent</mark>, respectively, from 2005 to 2012. Drinking in Massachussets, however, showed sharper changes, with a <mark class='mark--binge'>12.66 percent</mark> increase in binge drinking and a <mark class='mark--heavy'>21.3 percent</mark> increase in heavy drinking.</p>

